{{EngvarB|date=October 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Venice Elphi | fullname = Venice Elphi anak Danny Kaya | image = | image_size = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1984|9|10}}<ref>http://asia.eurosport.com/football/venice-elphi-ak-dannykaya_prs353595/person.shtml</ref> | birth_place = [[Kuching]], [[Sarawak]], [[Malaysia]] | height = {{height|meter=1.68}} | currentclub = [[ATM FA|ATM]] | clubnumber = 10 | position = [[Winger (soccer)|Winger]] | clubs1 = [[ATM FA|ATM]] | years1 = 2008– | caps1 = 128 | goals1 = 27 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | club-update = 19 December, 2017 | nationalteam-update = January 24, 2017 }}
'''Venice Elphi anak Danny Kaya''' (born 10 September 1984) is a [[Malaysia]]n footballer plays for [[ATM FA|Angkatan Tentera Malaysia]] in [[Malaysia FAM League]].<ref>http://www.nst.com.my/sports/soccer/let-s-salute-venice-today-1.103560</ref> Venice plays as a winger. As of 2016, he is the longest serving player in the current ATM FA squad.
==Career==
===ATM FA=== Venice football career started when his talent was spotted in 2007, two years after he joined the [[Malaysian Armed Forces]] in 2005. He was selected in [[ATM FA|the armed forces football team]] starting in 2008, when ATM FA was in the second-tier [[Malaysia Premier League]].<ref>http://www.atmfa.my/news/venice-mahu-nama-terus-disebut-di-pentas-bola-sepak-negara/</ref> Venice turned full-time professional with ATM FA in 2011, having played before that as a semi-professional player, combining soccer with his army duties.
Venice has won the [[2012 Malaysia Premier League]] with ATM FA, and were in the team that finished runners-up to [[Kelantan FA]] in the [[2012 Malaysia Cup]] final, the first time ATM FA qualified for the Malaysia Cup final since 1966.
2014 There's a rumour circuling around that he will be signed to play for his native Sarawak state. But it seems to be far from happened since his full time duty with atm unable to let him play for another team. Since his career with atm granted him job security even if he got injured and no longer to play anymore.
==International career== Venice received his first call-up to the [[Malaysia national football team]] in early 2012 under [[K. Rajagopal]].<ref>http://www.atmfa.my/news/daripada-ultra-ke-harimau-malaya-pembabitan-lewat-tidak-halang-venice-cipta-nama-dalam-skuad-malaysia/</ref>
==Personal== Venice was a Corporal in the Malaysian Armed Forces, before being promoted to Sergeant in 2012.<ref>http://www.sports247.my/2012/10/football-promotions-for-soldiers/</ref> He is of [[Iban people|Iban]]-[[Bidayuh]] native.<ref>http://www.utusan.com.my/utusan/Sukan/20121016/su_02/Koperal-Venice-Elphi-idam-juara</ref> 30 April 2018, He promoted to Staff Sergeant Venice Elphy.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/atmfanclub/posts/1677477512367585</ref>
